   PINE BROOK, N.J. -- Du Pont Co. and Du Pont Merck
Pharmaceutical Co., a joint venture between Du Pont and Merck
&amp; Co., scaled back their interest in the experimental
anti-cancer substance interleukin-1.
   The joint venture of the giant chemical concern and Merck
said it returned all rights over sales of therapeutic
products from interleukin-1 to Pine Brook-based Cistron
Biotechnology Inc.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The action is part of a contract among the three concerns
in which Du Pont will continue to purchase interleukin-1 from
Cistron for sale to research facilities at universities,
pharmaceutical concerns and government installations.
